- "Beating their sector's median market capitalization" implies the securities have a market capitalization higher than the middle value of their sector; 
- "Better price-to-earnings ratio than their sector's average" means the securities have a lower price-to-earnings ratio compared to the average of their sector, indicating they might be undervalued; 
- "Viewed at least 5 times on the same day" suggests popularity or interest in the securities; 
- "Top 10 securities per sector based on their dividend yield" implies a focus on high dividend-paying stocks within each sector.
